{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-10-26","name":"Margaret","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Margaret","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Margaret"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Margery","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1109–Female","fullLifespan":"Abt 1109–","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-97562-150-12/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/102778459","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-97562-150-12/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-904-97562-150-12/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Flag of England","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1109","birthPlace":{"address":"Yorkshire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.95878,"longitude":-1.08248,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Biography\nMargaret (Family Unknown) was the wife of Assulf de Notton.\n\nAssulf de Notton married Margaret (LNAB Unknown) and had Reginald who married a daughter of Lefwin fitzAviet.\n\nFarrer & Clay (1916), state that Robert, son of Lefwin, had a sister who married Reginald de Notton, and was the mother of Gilbert de Notton.\n\nConfirmation by Gilbert son of Reginald to the canons of Nostell of 2 bovates in Cramton, which Lefwin (son of Aviet), his grandfather, and Robert his son, the grantor's maternal uncle, gave.\n\nMargaret, wife of Assulf, held property in Notton.\n\nGilbert de Notton gave one bovate of land to Monk Bretton Priory, which Margaret the wife of Assulf formerly held.\n\nResearch Notes\nMargaret's LNAB is currently Unknown, and more research is needed to determine her Family.\n\nBased on the name of Lefwin, an old gedcom erroneously assigned Margaret to the family of Leofwin of Hindley, Lancashire, England. Ælfwine was the name of an ancient King of Deira, and there were several of that name living in England at this time.\n\nAssulf had assets in Yorkshire, whereas Hindley is in Lancashire.\n\nAssulf obtained 2 bovates in Notton from Robert, son of Lefwin. (It may be that a family tree linked Margaret to the Hindley family based on the name of Robert's father).","sourceList":[{"title":"genealogyonline: Holloway family tree","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.genealogieonline.nl/en/holloway-family-tree/P8096.php","sourceUri":"965M-V1R"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"1","year":"1109","date":"Abt 1109","place":"Yorkshire, England"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1138","date":"Abt 1138","place":"Notton, Yorkshire, England","age":"29","id":"GN87-75B"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1140","date":"about 1140","place":"Barton, Lancashire, England","age":"31","id":"LYSZ-YV5"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0"}],"spouse":[{"name":"Assulf de Notton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1105–Male","birthDate":"+1105","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/5cuxl/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"GCZP-8WD","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GCZP-8WD/assulf-de-notton-1105","published":true}],"children":[{"name":"Reginald De Notton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1138–1190","birthDate":"A+1138","deathDate":"+1190","age":52,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/wbuxl/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"otherParentId":"GCZP-8WD","@type":"Person","identifier":"GN87-75B","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GN87-75B/reginald-de-notton-1138-1190","published":true},{"name":"Julianna de Notton","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1140–Female","birthDate":"A+1140","otherParentId":"GCZP-8WD","@type":"Person","identifier":"LYSZ-YV5","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LYSZ-YV5/julianna-de-notton-1140","published":true}],"@type":"Person","@cont